  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Assembly_component_relationship 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship">
	 An <b>Assembly_component_relationship</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_usage"/>. 
It identifies a possibly quantified usage of a product version as a component of another product version.
<p>The relationship is established between two instances of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/>.</p>
<p>The inherited attribute <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.relating_view"/> identifies the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> of the assembly.</p>
<p>The inherited attribute <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.related_view"/> identifies the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> of the product version that plays the role of component.</p>
<p>The <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship"/> specifies that, in the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition.initial_context"/> of the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> that is referred to as <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.relating_view"/>, it is considered that the product version that is indirectly identified with the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.related_view"/> attribute, is a component of the product version that is indirectly identified with the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.relating_view"/> attribute.
</p>
<note number="1">In another context, the structure of the assembly may be described differently, adding, for example, an intermediate level between the products.</note>
<note number="2">This entity data type may be used to establish assembly relationships during design or to represent the composition of an assembly existing in the real world.</note>
<note number="3">An <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship"/> identifies an item in a parts list. Should the quantity be zero, the component would still be listed in the parts list.</note>

<p>In case the component is a <module_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:3_definition">part</module_ref>, the following additional specifications apply:</p>
<ul>
<li>the <b>quantity</b> attribute shall either be not specified or shall characterize a number of occurrences of the component;</li>
<li>if the <b>quantity</b> attribute specifies a number of occurrences, these occurrences shall be considered as a single group within the assembly structure;</li>
<li>if the <b>quantity</b> attribute is not specified, the relationship actually identifies a single occurrence of the component.</li>
</ul>
<p>In case the component is a <module_ref linkend="part_and_version_identification:3_definition">non-countable material</module_ref>, the following additional specifications apply:</p>
<ul>
<li>the <b>quantity</b> attribute shall either be not specified or shall characterize the amount of the material used as component;</li>
<li>if the <b>quantity</b> attribute is not specified, the amount of material used as component shall be considered as unknown.</li>

</ul>
<example>An assembly may require inclusion of ten grams of grease. 
</example>
<note number="4">This version of the Assembly structure module does not enable to represent the fact that the quantity of a fluid component is, 
for example 'at most 10 grams' or 'between 5 or 20 grams'. However, some ISO 10303 application protocols, for example ISO 10303-214, provide a representation for those requirements.</note>
<p>An <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship"/> shall be either a <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Next_assembly_usage"/>, a


 or a <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification"/>.</p>
</ext_description>


  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Assembly_component_relationship  Attribute: quantity 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship.quantity">
the <express_ref linkend="value_with_unit:arm:Value_with_unit_arm.Value_with_unit"/> that defines the amount of this usage of the component in the assembly. The value of this attribute need not be specified.
</ext_description>
  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Assembly_component_relationship  Attribute: location_indicator 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship.location_indicator">
	 the text that identifies this usage of the component in the assembly in a diagram, list, chart, or on a physical piece of
equipment. The value of this attribute need not be specified.
	 </ext_description>

<!--	   ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Assembly_component_relationship  Where: WR1 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship.wr:WR1">
If it is specified and if its value is expressed with a number, the quantity value shall be greater than zero.
	 </ext_description>
  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Next_assembly_usage 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Next_assembly_usage">
A <b>Next_assembly_usage</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship"/>.
It establishes a relationship between a component and its immediate parent assembly in a product structure.

</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Promissory_usage 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Promissory_usage">
A <b>Promissory_usage</b>
 is a type of <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship"/>. 
It establishes a relationship between an assembly and a component, regardless of the number of intermediate levels between them, which may be established with instances of <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Next_assembly_usage"/>.

<note>A  

<express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Promissory_usage"/>
 may be used when the product structure is not completely defined, to capture the intent that the constituent will
be used in that assembly.
</note>
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Component_upper_level_identification 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification">
A <b>Component_upper_level_identification</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship"/>. 
It identifies a component of an assembly with respect to an upper level in the assembly structure.
<note>A <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification"/> does not add a component in an assembly, it provides a means to further characterize a component with respect to an upper level assembly.
</note>
<example>A <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification"/> may be used to assign a property to a component that applies in the context of a particular upper level assembly.
</example>
<p>The identified component is the version of product, indirectly referred to as the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.related_view"/> of the <b>sub_assembly_relationship</b>.</p>
<p>The upper level assembly is the version of product, indirectly referred to as the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.relating_view"/> of the <b>upper_assembly_relationship</b>.</p>
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Component_upper_level_identification Attribute: upper_assembly_relationship
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification.upper_assembly_relationship">
the <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Assembly_component_relationship"/> that identifies indirectly the upper level assembly in the context of which the component is identified.

</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Component_upper_level_identification Attribute: sub_assembly_relationship
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification.sub_assembly_relationship">
the <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Next_assembly_usage"/> that identifies indirectly the component that is further characterized by the <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification"/>.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Component_upper_level_identification Unique: UR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification.ur:UR1">
the couple of the <b>upper_assembly_relationship</b> and <b>sub_assembly_relationship</b> attributes shall be unique.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Component_upper_level_identification Where: WR1
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification.wr:WR1">
the <b>upper_assembly_relationship</b> shall not refer to the <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification"/>.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Component_upper_level_identification Where: WR2
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification.wr:WR2">
the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.relating_view"/> attribute of the <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification"/> shall reference the same instance of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> as the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.relating_view"/> of the <b>upper_assembly_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Component_upper_level_identification Where: WR3
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification.wr:WR3">
the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.related_view"/> of the <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification"/> shall reference the same instance of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> as the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.related_view"/> for the <b>sub_assembly_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Component_upper_level_identification Where: WR4
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification.wr:WR4">
the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.related_view"/> of the <b>upper_assembly_relationship</b> shall refer to, or be transitively related to, the same instance of <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition:arm:Product_view_definition_arm.Product_view_definition"/> as the <express_ref linkend="product_view_definition_relationship:arm:Product_view_definition_relationship_arm.View_definition_relationship.relating_view"/> for the <b>sub_assembly_relationship</b>.
</ext_description>

  <!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Assembly_structure_arm  Entity: Component_upper_level_identification Where: WR5
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
   <ext_description linkend="Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification.wr:WR5">
the <b>upper_assembly_relationship</b> shall be an instance of either <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Next_assembly_usage"/> or of <express_ref linkend="assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Component_upper_level_identification"/>.
</ext_description>
